# Backend Conventions

- Keep handlers small: validate input, call services and return consistent responses.
- Put business logic in services or domain modules, not directly in handlers.
- Keep shared behavior in layers only when it is used by multiple APIs.
- Document public routes with OpenAPI or Swagger.
- Keep environment-specific values in config, SSM or Secrets Manager.
- Deploy shared layers before APIs when using the multi-API serverless preset.

